          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-01 15:49:58" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a close female associate of a group with well-defined membership (in the NT referring specifically to fellow believers in Christ)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>fellow believer</Gloss>
                <Gloss>sister in Christ</Gloss>
                <Gloss>sister in the faith</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though in a number of languages it is possible to use a term meaning ‘sister’ in the sense of a fellow believer, in some languages this cannot be done. As in the case of {L:ἀδελφός&lt;SDBG:ἀδελφός:000001&gt;}[b] (see {D:11.23}), it may be possible to use a term such as ‘relative,’ but more often than not, it may be necessary to use a phrase such as ‘one who also believes’ or ‘one who believes in Christ even as we do.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
